Here is a CSS only idea with `mix-blend-mode` where the trick is to have a pseudo element with background coloration that is below the sticky element covering all the space. When the element will start its sticky behavior, it will be above that area and the coloration will change.

Relevant code

    #timeline section.year {
      position:relative;
      background:#fff;
    }
    
    #timeline section.year:before {
        content: &quot;&quot;;
        position: absolute;
        top: 2em;
        left: 0;
        width: 50px;
        bottom: 1em;
        background: red;
        z-index: 2;
        mix-blend-mode: color;
    }

