In your `componentDidUpdate` you need to compare `prevProps` with current `props` before doing anything that can potentially change the current state of the component, otherwise you might end up having an infinite loop, as you can see on the documentation https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#componentdidupdate.

So your code should look like this:

    componentDidUpdate(prevProps) {
      if (prevProps.updateRequired !== this.props.updateRequired) {
        console.log(this.props);
        if (this.props.updateRequired === true) {
            this.anotherFunc();
        } else {
            console.log(&quot;update not required&quot;)
        }
      }    
    }

