As I wrote before the problem is that **SDL_PollEvent function is slower on Ubuntu than on Windows**.

This has pointed my attention on main loop and I found a problem: *new events polling is done on each loop on main while cycle* instead of on each frame (60 times per seconds) so this heavily slowdown the execution. This is not a problem on Windows because there is a sufficient time for drawing a frame each 16 ms but it is a problem on Ubuntu where SDL_PollEvent is slower and the frame is drawn not in time.

So **I moved the polling handler in order to check for a user input only 60 times per second. Don&#39;t put the polling function inside the main while loop without a robust control!**

